snippet.textDisplay: @Coke Studio Pakistan: Farsi is not pronounced this way! I am referring to the first line of this song. Farsi and Urdu are written in the same text (same alphabets) but  pronounced differently. The weight placed on words also varies significantly. Coke Studio Pakistan is doing a marvelous job, however, please ask your singer to listen to Farsi instead of reading it off paper and memorization - that way they can get the actual accent and then sing it according to the true Farsi pronunciation.
snippet.textOriginal: @Coke Studio Pakistan: Farsi is not pronounced this way! I am referring to the first line of this song. Farsi and Urdu are written in the same text (same alphabets) but  pronounced differently. The weight placed on words also varies significantly. Coke Studio Pakistan is doing a marvelous job, however, please ask your singer to listen to Farsi instead of reading it off paper and memorization - that way they can get the actual accent and then sing it according to the true Farsi pronunciation.
